quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  19,77,"Have you seen him who disbelieves in Our signs, and says, \"I shall surely be given wealth and children"
  19,78,"Has he become acquainted with the Unseen, or has he made a pact with the Beneficent"
  19,79,"Not so! We will write down what he says, and We will extend for him a span of torment"
  19,80,"And We will make him inherit that whereof he spoke, and he shall come to Us alone"
  19,81,They take other gods besides Allah to be their source of power
  19,82,"Not so! They shall deny their worship of them, and shall become their opponents"
  19,83,"Do you not see that We have sent the devils against the disbelievers, to confound them with confusion"
  19,84,"So be not you hasty with them. Verily, We do but number them a sum (of days)"
  19,85,"On the Day when We will gather the righteous unto the Beneficent, honoured as a goodly company"
  19,86,"We will drive the guilty into hell, like thirsty herds to water"
  19,87,"They shall have no power of intercession, save him who has taken a covenant with his Lord"
  19,88,"They say, \"The Beneficent has taken to Himself a son"
  19,89,"Assuredly, you have brought a monstrous thing"
  19,90,"Whereby the heavens are almost torn asunder, and the earth is riven, and the mountains fall in ruin"
  19,91,That you attribute to the Beneficent a son
  19,92,When it is not becoming to the majesty of the Beneficent that he take to Himself a son
  19,93,There is none in the heavens or the earth but comes to the Beneficent as a servant
  19,94,"Verily, He knows them and numbers them exactly"
  19,95,"And each one of them come unto Him on the Day of Resurrection, alone"